    "medgen_uid": "41345",
    "disease_name": "5p partial monosomy syndrome",
    "concept_id": "C0010314",
    "disease_type": "Disease or Syndrome",
    "definition": "Cri-du-chat syndrome was first described by Lejeune et al. (1963) as a hereditary congenital syndrome associated with deletion of part of the short arm of chromosome 5. The deletions can vary in size from extremely small and involving only band 5p15.2 to the entire short arm. Although the majority of deletions arise as new mutations, approximately 12% result from unbalanced segregation of translocations or recombination involving a pericentric inversion in one of the parents. [from OMIM ]",
    "synonyms": [
      "5p deletion syndrome",
      "5p- syndrome",
      "CAT CRY SYNDROME",
      "CHROMOSOME 5p DELETION SYNDROME",
      "Cri du Chat Syndrome"
    ],
